(thirdQuint)Growth Hormone Treatment of Women With Turner Syndrome.

 This study is a randomised, double-blinded, controlled clinical trial to evaluate the effect of growth hormone (GH) treatment on adult women with Turner syndrome.

 The endpoints will be changes in body composition and heart function evaluated by echocardiography (ECHO) and positron emission tomography (PET).

 Phase one: 6 months of GH or placebo treatment.

 Phase two: "open label" all participants are treated with GH for 12 months.

 At baseline, healthy controls will be examined, but will not receive any treatment.

